JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 453
EP  - 459
VL  - 5
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The problem studied is that of how to allocate a fixed amount of some resource among various activities where, after a period of time, unused portions of the resource lose their value. Demand for the resource at each station is considered to be random. The problem is a special case of one usually referred to as the distribution of the effort. The question of determining the optimal amount of resource is also discussed.
